Kafka Start process: To start kafka, we need to start Zookeeper then start Kafka server.

Open Command Prompt:1
------------------------
Step1)To start Zookeeper from command line run below command:-
C:\kafka_2.13-3.5.1>bin\windows\zookeeper-server-start.bat config\zookeeper.properties
after run the command, for comfirmation see the result:[2023-09-15 10:39:45,888] INFO binding to port 0.0.0.0/0.0.0.0:2181 (org.apache.zookeeper.server.NIOServerCnxnFactory)

Open Command Prompt:2
------------------------
Step2)Then Start the kafka server in different command prompt..use below command
C:\kafka_2.13-3.5.1>bin\windows\kafka-server-start.bat config\server.properties
In got one error..see below
C:\kafka_2.13-3.5.1>bin\windows\kafka-server-start.bat config\server.properties
'wmic' is not recognized as an internal or external command,
operable program or batch file.

To REsolve this issue..I open kafka-server-start.bat and modify with below..
IF [%1] EQU [] (
    echo USAGE: %0 server.properties
    EXIT /B 1
)

SetLocal

rem --- Set Log4j options ---
IF ["%KAFKA_LOG4J_OPTS%"] EQU [""] (
    set KAFKA_LOG4J_OPTS=-Dlog4j.configuration=file:%~dp0../../config/log4j.properties
)

rem --- Set heap memory manually (Modern Windows fix) ---
IF ["%KAFKA_HEAP_OPTS%"] EQU [""] (
    rem You can change values if you want more or less memory
    set KAFKA_HEAP_OPTS=-Xmx512M -Xms256M
)

"%~dp0kafka-run-class.bat" kafka.Kafka %*
EndLocal

After save this file ..again re-run the command..
C:\kafka_2.13-3.5.1>bin\windows\kafka-server-start.bat config\server.properties
=>yes..finally kafka also started...

